                    <span>I must admit I was quite skeptical even after I read all the reviews on the book. This was recommended by our Operations prof at MBA school. 
<br />
<br />The book is an extremely easy read, fast paced and well written. He does a great job to illustrate the essence of the theory of constraints using real world simple examples.
<br />
<br />Strongly recommend to anyone remotely interested in process engineering or even just general reading. (The concept is probably being subconsiously used in your everyday life to help prioritize your tasks)</span>
                  
              
